text: Tibbee Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Tibbee is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "icy water". Variant names are "Oktibbeha Creek", "Tibbee River", and "Tibby Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Clay County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Lowndes County, Mississippi
title: Tibbee Creek
